examples.en: Women have become a force to be reckoned with.
He reckoned the odds are against the scheme going ahead.
Have you reckoned in the members who are absent?
Losses were reckoned to be over a million dollars.
The Lowsons were reckoned to be very good farmers.
A good-natured man, but reckoned near. (Mrs. Delany)
The principal was certainly a woman to be reckoned with.
An earthquake of magnitude 7 is reckoned as a major quake.
Barcelona will be a force to be reckoned with this season.
The new teacher soon had the class reckoned up and was able to control them.
The expression 'full moon' means the fourteenth day of the moon reckoned from its first appearance.
He was reckoned one of the richest merchants in the city.
I had not reckoned with the excitement in the popular press.
They reckoned that they would reach their destination by noon.
Moving house is reckoned to be nearly as stressful as divorce.
The Christian age is usually reckoned from the birth of Christ.
The elephant is reckoned the slowest breeder of all known animals.
He got more than he reckoned for when he chose to play against such an opponent.
The average selling price for flats in the area was reckoned to be around 11,000.
He's a quick and decisive player  a force to be reckoned with (=a person, team, company etc that influences what happens).
